 to the generosity of the Jackson Hope Fund  Faculty Expertise 100  of VMI full time faculty in degree granting departments hold the Ph D  They are renowned for teaching excellence  mentorship of students  scholarly engagement and expertise  commitment to service  and encouragement of undergraduate research  Faculty Profile    RANK   Professors 62   Associate Professors 26   Assistant Professors 40   Instructors 3     DEGREE   Doctoral Degrees 128     TENURE   Tenured 81   Tenure Track 32   Non Tenure Track 9   FULL TIME PART TIME Total Faculty  Excluding ROTC  131 60  Data as of May 2014 VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Virginia Military Institute   Faculty Development    Virginia Military Institute   Faculty Development                       skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institute Honors Program International Programs Service Opportunities Summer Programs